*Grid
*Unified shape that is replaced with individual squares
*Use the grid to see if a row is full
    *Shift all rows above, sequentially
*Game is over when a block can't enter the screen without intersecting an existing piece
New level at certain score
High level = faster falling
*Only fall the number of rows of how many were removed
*Up = rotate
*Down = fall faster
*Right/Left = move
*New pieces start completely visible in the middle of the top of the grid
Collision detection to make sure that they don't rotate through walls, other pieces
*Preview of next piece to fall
*Randomized pieces
*I, J, L, O, S, T, and Z